@Task


@Task
The @Task decorator tells Twist to execute a method as part of its task queue. It takes a numerical priority as an argument, which determines the order that tasks are run in (tasks with lower numbers for their priority are run first).
Usage:
class C {
    @Task(priority)
    myMethod() {

    }
}

pages/reference/decorators/Throttle.html.body:
Table of Contents  generated with DocToc

@Throttle


@Throttle
The @Throttle decorator is used to throttle the application of a method when it's invoked, so that it's only executed at most once in a given time period (which is passed as an argument to the decorator, in milliseconds). This provides the same functionality as the Lodash Throttle utility.
Usage:
class C {
    @Throttle(wait)
    method() {

    }
}

As an example, if wait is 1000 (1 second), then the following code will result in method being called precisely twice, with a 1 second delay between each call:
var c = new C();
c.method();
c.method();
c.method();

