The  structural component allows you to iterate over the contents of a collection. There are two different ways of using :

Use the for attribute to bind to an expression of the form  in , e.g. for={ item in list }.
Use the collection attribute to bind to an expression that evaluates to an array, and the as attribute to specify a variable to assign each item to (this is the same use of as as the using component uses).

Here's an example with :
var fruits = [ "apple", "orange", "watermelon" ];
export default 

        { item }

;

And here's the same example with :
var fruits = [ "apple", "orange", "watermelon" ];
export default 

        { item }

;

In both cases, this renders the following in the DOM (the  component is virtual, so it doesn't appear in the DOM):

    apple
    orange
    watermelon


Note that if the array contents can change, you need to use an ObservableArray in order for reactivity to work - otherwise, Twist won't know to re-render when items in the list change.

